                            <comment id="17314195" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Sat, 3 Apr 2021 05:54:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Although separate problems we should fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2927&quot; title=&quot;ErrorHandlers on Appenders cannot be configured.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-2927&quot;&gt;LOG4J2-2927&lt;/a&gt; at the same time.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17314257" author="noobgam" created="Sat, 3 Apr 2021 12:48:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hm. In our case we managed to just call &lt;em&gt;.setHandler()&lt;/em&gt;, doesn&apos;t this resolve the issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/master/log4j-core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/appender/AbstractAppender.java#L260&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/master/log4j-core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/appender/AbstractAppender.java#L260&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 There already is a method that allows you to configure errorHandler post-construction. This indeed seems odd to configure it this way, but I fail to see how these issues are related at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the case of AbstractAppender you can call this method in the constructor of the superclass before it is started&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
